1st time to a Capital Grille steakhouse. This one is located in Indianapolis, IN. Being my first there I decided to have the valet done by the hotel of Capital Grille. Very awesome valet and gave me a nice refreshing bottled water. Valet was under $20 that time I arrived. Nice foyer as your walking towards the next set of doors. I was greeted by a very sweet host, Katelyn(my apologies if I misspelled). I was allowed to choose the bar, high tables or traditional seating level. Decided the high tables for lunch. Ordered the following: ribeye done in medium paired with a glass of pinot grigo(I appreciate your recommendations, Katelyn). Finished up with Caramelized crusted cheesecake. Had the onion soup with Havarti(or was it Gouda) on top, to go. Overall, 4.9 🌟 stars out of 5. The truffle French fries, I was hoping to have some tiny pieces of truffle, however, I think it was simply cooked with truffle oil. Every piece of food or drink was greater than par with an exception to the truffle fries(bogey +). Katelyn, I think you are an excellent host! 👌 I should of ask if they had Chicago style steak seasoning. Couple minutes prior to doneness and seasoning will be perfect after a nice rest. To the Capital Grille, much appreciation for a delightful time and atmosphere for lunch. I strongly want to experience their breakfast setting. To my Ku'uiPo ViVi, i apologized I snuck away from you to experience some alone time for this one.  -marlon sends

I cannot say enough about this restaurant. Last evening was my second visit and it was just as wonderful as the first. The atmosphere is so pleasant and the service is so friendly. Dave was very prompt about greeting us when we arrived to be seated and quickly got us water and drinks. I typically refuse to sit near the kitchen, but we were seated there last evening and it wasn’t so bad at Capital Grille. The kitchen wasn’t overly loud and the staff weren’t so boisterous as I’ve encountered in the past elsewhere. Our server was John. He was knowledgeable and informative about the menu options and specials. We started with the pan fried calamari. Oh, my! There was just so much of it! It was cooked to perfection and the pieces were of good size. Each piece was buttery delicious. My husband ordered rack of lamb and ordered salmon prepared Oscar style. We also ordered asparagus and lobster mac n’ cheese. The main course was just so fantastic! The lamb was cooked perfectly medium rare, as ordered, and the flavor was just delicious. My salmon was even more enjoyable than I anticipated. The sides were delightful, too. Now if you’ve never had lobster mac n’ cheese, you need to absolutely taste Capital Grille’s take on it. So heavenly! We were celebrating my husbands birthday and John was most accommodating helping me do something special. The plate John brought out had Happy Birthday stenciled on it in chocolate and contained a small round serving of flourless espresso cake and another small round serving of cheesecake, with some slices of fruit. All were fantastic! The photos of the food don’t do it justice. If you’ve never been, know that the all-around experience is certainly worth the expense. The food will knock your socks off!!

They had a single long stem rose, a hand written card wishing us Happy Anniversary & all servers signed their name to it & heart confetti on the table. Me & my husband both ordered steaks which were cooked perfectly & great! We also shared the lobster Mac & cheese, which is to die for! Seriously the best lobster Mac & cheese we have ever had!! The good - Great atmosphere and location. Great drinks. The bad -  three people at the table ordered 10 oz. Filets, all cooked to different temperatures. All three were undercooked by at least a magnitude of two. Which, ok, you can always send your steak back to be cooked more but at this level/price of restaurant, I expected them to know how to cook a steak. In addition, two of the steaks appeared to be sized correctly, the third steak was  much smaller and looked  more like a 6 oz, which was frustrating. My biggest concern was one of sanitation.  We had three different assistant servers stop by to fill our water glasses, only one did it properly by picking up the glass at the base. The other two put their hands around the rim of the glass. This may not be an issue to others but I am a slight germaphobe and it was very disconcerting to me. Since this happened with 2 out of the 3 assistants, it's clearly a systemic issue and makes me question their other sanitary practices.
